events.description: Release of preliminary estimates for Finland's trade balance in December 2025 and the full-year 2025 summary.

facts.fact_text: Finland's trade deficit narrowed to EUR 0.21 billion in December 2025 from EUR 0.22 billion in the previous year.

evidences.evidence_text: Finland’s trade deficit narrowed slightly to EUR 0.21 billion in December 2025 from EUR 0.22 billion a year earlier, according to preliminary estimates.

facts.fact_text: Exports increased by 0.4% year-on-year to reach EUR 6 billion in December 2025.

evidences.evidence_text: Exports rose 0.4% year-on-year to EUR 6 billion

facts.fact_text: Imports rose by 0.3% to EUR 6.2 billion in December 2025.

evidences.evidence_text: Meanwhile, imports also increased by 0.3% to EUR 6.2 billion

facts.fact_text: Finland's cumulative trade deficit for the full year 2025 was EUR 0.86 billion.

evidences.evidence_text: For full-year 2025, Finland recorded a cumulative trade deficit of EUR 0.86 billion, narrowing sharply from EUR 2.7 billion in the previous year.

claims.claim_text: The growth in exports was primarily fueled by a significant rise in trade with non-EU countries.
claims.author: Preliminary estimates

evidences.evidence_text: Exports rose 0.4% year-on-year to EUR 6 billion, driven by a sharp 12.6% increase to non-EU countries.

evidence.evidence_text: Exports rose 0.4% year-on-year to EUR 6 billion, driven by a sharp 12.6% increase to non-EU countries.
